## Inputs and Outputs

| Port | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| `video_in` | GL Texture | Source Video A (base) |
| `video_b_in` | GL Texture | Source Video B (what gets moshed/displaced) |
| `depth_in` | GL Texture | Depth map used for edge extraction |
| `video_out`| GL Texture | Output |

---

## Edge Cases and Error Handling

- **Missing Depth Input**: Bypasses edge extraction, either halting the mosh effect or applying a uniform fallback without crashing (SAFETY RAIL #7).
- **FBO Cleanup**: Requires feedback FBOs for the `fracture_decay` (persistent cracks) and the datamosh itself. Both sets must be deleted on unload (SAFETY RAIL #8).

